 148:Core/Src/freertos.c ****   /* vApplicationIdleHook() will only be called if configUSE_IDLE_HOOK is set
 149:Core/Src/freertos.c ****   to 1 in FreeRTOSConfig.h. It will be called on each iteration of the idle
 150:Core/Src/freertos.c ****   task. It is essential that code added to this hook function never attempts
 151:Core/Src/freertos.c ****   to block in any way (for example, call xQueueReceive() with a block time
 152:Core/Src/freertos.c ****   specified, or call vTaskDelay()). If the application makes use of the
 153:Core/Src/freertos.c ****   vTaskDelete() API function (as this demo application does) then it is also
 154:Core/Src/freertos.c ****   important that vApplicationIdleHook() is permitted to return to its calling
 155:Core/Src/freertos.c ****   function, because it is the responsibility of the idle task to clean up
 156:Core/Src/freertos.c ****   memory allocated by the kernel to any task that has since been deleted. */
